    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overread in eAxC ID configuration when using custom categories\n\n### Summary\nThe `set_fh_eaxcid_conf` function in the O-RAN fronthaul configuration could cause a segmentation fault when called with invalid category values. The function did not properly validate input parameters before dereferencing pointers.\n\nThis issue occurred when users attempted to configure custom eAxC ID mappings through modified configuration paths. The original function would attempt to write to uninitialized memory locations when passed NULL pointers or invalid category enums.\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/fhi_72/oran-config.c`: Added NULL pointer validation and structure initialization in `set_fh_eaxcid_conf`\n- `radio/fhi_72/oran-config.c`: Added `set_fh_eaxcid_conf_custom` for flexible eAxC ID configuration\n- `radio/fhi_72/oran-params.h`: Added configurable RU category parameter\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Modify configuration to expose `set_fh_eaxcid_conf` function externally\n2. Call function with NULL pointer: `set_fh_eaxcid_conf(NULL, XRAN_CATEGORY_A)`\n3. Observe segmentation fault due to direct pointer dereference\n4. Alternatively, call with invalid category enum value outside expected range\n5. Function would return false without clear indication of failure reason\n\nThe fix ensures proper error handling and prevents crashes when invalid parameters are provided, while maintaining backward compatibility with existing configurations.\n"
}